# The parenthesized `(and ...)`/`(or ...)` forms are the variadic/alternate-arity call per
# spec/grammar.md:165 ("a variadic or alternate-arity call must be wrapped in parentheses");
# the parser's parenthesized-call reader special-cases `and`/`or` so they gather every operand
# up to the closing `)` into one ParenCall node, rather than requiring exactly two like the
# infix form (packages/parser/src/parser.ts parseParenthesized).
:a = true
:b = false
:c = true
print (and :a :b :c)
print (or :a :b)
print (and :a)
